The edits you made to this seem to have improved it overall. It's still a thing that can potentially end the world/universe though and that stuff is still tiring to me, not less than it was before. So because of that, I just could not really enjoy reading this or get into it; a thing that can end the universe without anything truly special to it is going to exhaust me.

That said, the final addendum has given me serious pause about how to vote because it really ties together what you're working for in this article (that is, if I'm reading into it as well as you want people to). Plus, it's a pretty special element to the article and helps separate it from other similar end-of-universe stuff. It might come down to a matter of personal enjoyment versus letting your craft and skill at single-article storytelling convince me to novote instead. You sure wrote something to think on, and I think this article is the kind of thing people should read when they want to attempt similar ideas and themes.





