14 Dec 2017 15:30






djkaktus, I'm a new member here, and I've been overawed by many of your posts; they are what inspired me to try to write an SCP, and I think they're just as good as a lot of the old classics.

I don't like this one as much, though. The polish and writing and images are impeccable, but there are just no restrictions on the power of the anomaly. I think that what an anomaly cannot do is more interesting than what it can do. But it seems like this is essentially a super-omnipotent being, not only omnipotent in its own world/narrative, but in all others, with nothing capable of being greater than it, able to alter all realities to its own will.

It's like a painting that is nothing but a square of gold foil: with no negative space to contrast with, it's not as interesting as a painting where gold foil is used to highlight.

So I downvoted it; I don't know the usual rules of voting, so if this isn't the way it's supposed to work, let me know and I'll change my vote.







